Intuition
When i looked at this problem i realized it is a sliding window problem with dynamic window size , so my key intition was i will calculate the target freq map of string t and then i will create window _freq map for string s , now i will create a variable formed to see if my window is formed with required charcaaters from target freq and when the condition meets i will check the size of window store the size of smallest window and store the smallest possible string in result . i only update result if find a substring of length smaller than my currently stored window after shrinking , then shrink the window and see if i can find the smallest possible string with valid conditions , return the answer .

